modules.description: Provides functions to construct and manipulate a tree-based layout of text elements, including padded and unpadded concatenation and line-break annotations. Operates on inductive data structures representing source code elements, such as expressions, statements, and type declarations. Used to generate compact, readable source code output by dynamically adjusting line breaks based on a specified width constraint.

This module enables the construction and manipulation of an embedded domain-specific language (eDSL) for document formatting, supporting operations like text insertion, layout control, and element composition through structured document components. It works with internal representations such as abstract syntax trees and document objects, allowing for hierarchical nesting and operator-based combinations. Specific use cases include generating typeset outputs, dynamically adjusting layout structures, and creating reusable formatting patterns.
